      "writtenOn": "2021-02-22T22:31:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t like how everything is unnecessary tightly coupled. There\u0027s no need to put the error reporting client in the context. There\u0027s actually no need to modify existing logging code at all, just add some new. \n\nI propose to:\n\n1. To go.chromium.org/luci/common/logging/sdlogger add CloudErrorsSink implementing LogEntryWriter interface:\n\n  type CloudErrorsSink struct {\n    Client *errorreporting.Client\n    Out LogEntryWriter\n  }\n\n  func (s *CloudErrorsSink) Write(e *LogEntry) {\n    if e.Severity \u003d\u003d ErrorSeverity {\n      // report via e.Client\n    }\n    s.Out.Write(e)\n  }\n\n2. In https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/refs/heads/master/server/server.go#1293 wrap \u0026severityTracker with \u0026sdlogger.CloudErrorsSink{...} if Cloud Error reporting it enabled.",
      "revId": "5c9f541b88a2c481ef13cbf8a96074b144b00c51",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b0e98b04_98fdd504",
        "filename": "common/logging/sdlogger/logger.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 233,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-22T22:31:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Flushing on every error is excessive. Imagine something in cr-buildbucket breaks and it logs an error for every request at 1000 QPS (it is totally possible). And now we have not only broken Buildbucket, but also a Buildbucket that makes 1000 QPS to Cloud Error reporting (which may in turn also \"break\", e.g. due to quota issues).\n\nBuffering errors is fine, it is the primary advantage of using cloud.google.com/go/errorreporting instead of calling the API on our own.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 233,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 233,
        "endChar": 14
      },
      "revId": "5c9f541b88a2c481ef13cbf8a96074b144b00c51",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e919ce05_dd91a324",
        "filename": "common/logging/sdlogger/logger.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 236,
