        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-20T10:03:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s hard to write unit tests for this piece of code as errorreport.Client is a struct of an interface. Unable to mock it. So I think we can skip the unit tests. I tested it in dev which worked well. Even if the client is not set in Context, it will just skip and won\u0027t cause any errors.",
      "revId": "5c9f541b88a2c481ef13cbf8a96074b144b00c51",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
